<p>You can extend the size of a volume, as needed.</p>
<section>
<title>
<!-- id="extend-a-volume" -->
<!-- id="extend-a-volume" -->Extend a volume</title>
<ol>
<li>
<p>
<xref href="../../../../../../commercial/GA1/CarrierGrade/UseCases/carrier-grade.dashboard.launch.dita" >Launch the HP Helion OpenStack Helion Dashboard</xref>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click the <b>Project</b> dashboard, then the <b>System</b> panel, then the <b>Volumes</b> link.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <b>Volumes</b> screen, for the volume you want to extend,  click the arrow icon in the <b>Actions</b> menu and select <b>Extend Volume</b>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <b>Extend Volume</b> dialog box, enter a larger size (in GB) in the <b>New Size</b> field. The new size must be larger than the current size.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click <b>Extend Volume</b> to confirm.</p>
</li>
</ol>
